R8-E3 integration: a GLOBAL fixed-beta anchor blend for quality/layered mode.
DEFAULT-OFF -> byte-identical (anchor_blend_beta absent/None skips the blend entirely;
region_aware and every other path unchanged). This is NOT the local-adaptive-beta the
thread set out to land (that is a measured NO-GO -- see REPORT.md); it is the simpler,
stronger result the experiment surfaced: out = compact + beta*(x4plus - compact) with a
single global beta=0.85 is <= x4plus on EVERY (window x degrade) cell of the R6-E1 matrix
(5 windows x 3 operators) AND on a real-H.264 OOD spot-check, strictly better on
smooth/moderate-degrade content (mean -5.7%, smooth-moderate -8.9% TRUE LPIPS). It closes
R6-E3's filed open item: the fix for "fixed-0.5 loses on gritty" is a more conservative
constant (0.85), not adaptivity. beta=0.50 (R6-E3) regresses up to +0.0195 LPIPS on
textured/gritty content; 0.85 does not regress under either operator family.

Cost: the COMPACT anchor cache already exists (region_gate["compact"], built for the
region-aware output blend) -> the blend is ONE per-frame CPU lerp, ZERO extra SR.

SEAM (verified by verify_patch.py): caller `derisk.blend_anchor_cache(perframe_cache,
region_gate["compact"], beta)` -> handler `def blend_anchor_cache(heavy_cache,
compact_cache, beta)`; both caches are dict[int]->HxWx3 uint8 at HD, identical keys,
identical shapes; in-place, returns the same dict. blend math == the measured eval math.

NB (honest scope, same discipline as R6-E3/R7-E2): the win is measured on the ANCHOR
(single-frame degrade-restore SR, TRUE LPIPS). The propagation/temporal (tOF) effect of
pre-blending anchors before MV warp is UNMEASURED -> ship default-OFF, flip to 0.85 only
after an integrated propagation+tOF A/B.

